<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, viewport-fit=cover" />
    <base href="/" />
    @* Inter font — loaded from Google Fonts with swap for no FOUT.
       The 'Inter Variable' axis font covers 100–900 weight in one file.
       display=swap ensures text remains visible during webfont load. *@
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:opsz,wght@14..32,400..800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="_content/MudBlazor/MudBlazor.min.css" />
    @* Phase 5 — Bootstrap removal: the Bootstrap CSS link is gone.
       The lib/bootstrap directory was deleted from wwwroot/. Any
       remaining Bootstrap utility classes are now served from scoped
       CSS files (Components/Account/Shared/AccountLayout.razor.css for
       the static-SSR identity forms, Components/Shared/AssignmentCalendar.razor.css
       for the calendar pills, Components/Shared/GameDayCalendar.razor.css
       for the list-group equivalents). MudBlazor's utility classes
       (pa-*, ma-*, d-flex, align-center, ms-*, me-*, etc.) cover the
       rest of the app. *@
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="@Assets["app.css"]" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="@Assets["ServantSync.styles.css"]" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="@Assets["css/snake.css"]" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="@Assets["css/fishfling.css"]" />
    <ImportMap />
    @* Branding assets — see BRANDING.md for the design rationale and
       color tokens. The SVG mark is the favicon (modern browsers all
       render SVG favicons natively via type="image/svg+xml"). The
       apple-touch-icon links the 180×180 PNG rasterization for iOS
       home-screen pinning (iOS Safari ignores SVG apple-touch-icons).
       The PNG was rendered from the SVG via headless Chrome at
       --window-size=180,180 --default-background-color=00000000 so the
       alpha channel survives; see wwwroot/img/README.md for the
       regeneration steps. The theme-color is the navbar's actual
       rendered tint, not the brand indigo, so the address bar doesn't
       seam against the dark navbar on first paint. *@
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="@Assets["img/servantsync-mark.svg"]" />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href="@Assets["img/apple-touch-icon.png"]" />
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#0d0d1f" />
    <script src="js/snake.js" defer></script>
    <script src="js/fishfling.js" defer></script>
    @* Round-CHAPEL-DRAWER-1: responsive drawer toggle + resize watcher.
       The drawer is a plain <aside> controlled by CSS class .ss-drawer-open
       on <body>.  No Blazor interop — pure JS that works in static SSR
       before the SignalR circuit warms up.  Resize watcher auto-syncs
       the class when the viewport crosses 600px. *@
    <script src="js/livedrawer.js" defer></script>
    <HeadOutlet />
</head>

<body>
    <Routes />
    <script src="_content/MudBlazor/MudBlazor.min.js"></script>
    <script src="_framework/blazor.web.js"></script>
</body>

</html>
